  "passageParts": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Weighing yourself regularly is a wonderful way to stay aware of any significant weight fluctuations.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, when done too often, this habit can sometimes hurt more than it\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​.\n As for me, weighing myself every day caused me to shift my focus from being generally healthy and physically active to focusing\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\non the scale. That was bad to my overall fitness goals. I had gained weight in the form of muscle mass, but thinking only of\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe number on the scale, I altered my training program. That conflicted with how I needed to train to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nmy goals.\n I also found weighing myself daily did not provide an accurate\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof the hard work and progress I was making in the gym. It takes about three weeks to a month to notice significant changes in weight\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\naltering your training program. The most\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nchanges will be observed in skill level, strength and inches lost.\n For these\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, I stopped weighing myself every day and switched to a bimonthly weighing schedule\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​. Since weight loss is not my goal, it is less important for me to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nmy weight each week. Weighing every other week allows me to observe and\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nany significant weight changes. That tells me whether I need to\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 13
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nmy training program.\n I also use my bimonthly weigh-in\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nto get information about my nutrition as well. If my training intensity remains the same, but I'm constantly\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nand dropping weight, this is a\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthat I need to increase my daily caloric intake.\n The\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nto stop weighing myself every day has done wonders for my overall health, fitness and well-being. I am experiencing increased zeal for working out since I no longer carry the burden of a\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 18
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nmorning weigh-in. I've also experienced greater success in achieving my specific fitness goals,\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 19
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nI'm training according to those goals, instead of numbers on a scale.\n Rather than\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nover the scale, turn your focus to how you look, feel, how your clothes fit and your overall energy level."
    }
  ],
